                android:text="Beef Tapa:

In a bowl, combine soy sauce, oyster sauce, brown sugar, minced garlic, calamansi juice, and black pepper. Mix well to create the marinade.

Add the thinly sliced beef to the marinade, ensuring each piece is well-coated. Marinate for at least 30 minutes to 2 hours in the refrigerator.

Heat cooking oil in a pan over medium-high heat. Fry the marinated beef until browned and fully cooked. Set aside.

Garlic Fried Rice (Sinangag):

In a large pan or wok, heat cooking oil over medium heat.

Add minced garlic and sauté until golden brown and fragrant.

Add the day-old cooked rice to the pan. Break up any clumps and stir-fry until the rice is heated through.

Season with salt to taste and continue stirring until the rice is well-coated with the garlic-infused oil.

Fried Egg (Itlog):

In a separate pan, heat cooking oil over medium heat.

Crack an egg into the pan. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Fry the egg to your desired level of doneness, whether it's over easy, medium, or well-done.

Assembling Tapsilog:

Plate a serving of garlic fried rice.

Top with a portion of the cooked beef tapa.

Serve with a fried egg on the side.

Optionally, garnish with additional calamansi or lemon wedges."
